cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about learning control policies for manipulation tasks, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses neural networks for policy representation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning to train the policies, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the method on simulated and real-world tasks, which may involve computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
